It appears that *related_blog_posts* doesn't work on Internet Explorer, on any blog/portal. I created a plain blog template on my portal, added in the snippet `{% related_blog_posts limit=3 %}` and while it shows on other browsers on IE11 it gives the error:
```&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;
  fetch('/_hcms/related-blog-posts?blogPostId=10435932112&amp;blogId=5897119826&amp;targetBlogPostIds=10435932112&amp;macro=default&amp;limit=3&amp;templatePath=generated_layouts%2F27315590401.html&amp;contentId=10435932112&amp;hs-expires=1622753082&amp;hs-version=1&amp;hs-signature=AM6Wq0ar4UM0_UxDSAKzWC-erF0zIaUojQ').then(response =&gt; {
    if (response.ok) {
      return response.text();
    } else {
      console.log('Could not fetch related blog posts');
      return Promise.resolve('');
    }
  }).then(data =&gt; {
    document.getElementById('related-blog-posts-5393411591217082467').outerHTML = data;
  })
  .catch((error) =&gt; {
    console.error('Error:', error);
  });
&lt;/script&gt;```
Post link <http://sogaygarcia-1951013.hs-sites.com/test-blog/praesent-dapibus-laoreet-gravida|here>. Who can I report this to? I personally can't wait to stop supporting IE11 but it might be an issue for my client, they did point it out :disappointed:
